  "text": "Quantum state redistribution. In the task of quantum state redistribution Alice, Bob, and a referee share a total pure state |ψ RABC , where Alice initially holds the particles AC and Bob holds the particle B. The aim of the task is to send the particle C from Alice to Bob in such a way that the overall state |ψ remains intact. For achieving this, Alice and Bob can use quantum communication at rate Q and singlets at rate E. This task was first introduced in [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , and it has been shown that the process is possible if and only if",
